.TH "mode_show" 9 "mode_show" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mode_show \- presents the current mode of the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" mode_show
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Generic device associated with the device.
.IP "attr" 12
Device attribute representing the device mode.
.IP "buf" 12
Buffer of length PAGE_SIZE to report back the dev mode in ASCII.
.SH "RETURN"
The size of the ASCII string returned in \fIbuf\fP.
